In this section, we briefly review related work on aspect-based opinion mining .
 The most related work to ours is the work of @cite  .
 In this work, the authors propose a method to extract opinion targets from user reviews .
 In their work, they use a dependency parser and a syntactic dependency parser to extract target words .
 In this paper, we compare the proposed method with the existing methods in the following aspects: 1) we propose a confirmatory aspect based opinion mining framework, 2) we use a part-of-speech tagger to match user reviews to a pre-specified topic, and 3) we evaluate our method on a set of user reviews obtained from TripAdvisor .
 Sentiment analysis in Twitter has been studied for a long time .
 @cite proposed a probabilistic modeling framework based on Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA), which detects sentiment and topic simultaneously from text .
 The proposed JST model is fully unsupervised and is evaluated on a new gold standard dataset, which contains three types of reviews, i .
